WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:03.378
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:03.461 --> 00:05.046
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:05.130 --> 00:07.966
{\an7}♪ ADVENTURE IS CALLING,
SHE CAN'T STAY AWAY ♪

00:08.048 --> 00:11.594
{\an7}♪ HER ARMOR IS SPARKLING,
HER COURAGE IS GREAT ♪

00:11.678 --> 00:15.348
{\an7}♪ HER NECKLACE IS GLOWING,
NOW SHE'LL FIND A WAY ♪

00:15.432 --> 00:17.100
{\an7}♪ WITH HELP FROM
HER BEST FRIENDS ♪

00:17.183 --> 00:18.935
{\an8}♪ THEY'LL SAVE THE DAY ♪

00:19.018 --> 00:20.687
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:20.770 --> 00:22.647
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:22.731 --> 00:26.234
{\an7}♪ TRUE TO HERSELF,
DOING WHAT'S RIGHT ♪

00:26.317 --> 00:27.694
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:27.777 --> 00:30.864
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:34.200 --> 00:36.119
COACH: OK, STUDENTS.

00:36.202 --> 00:38.455
IF A FIRE-BREATHING
DRAGON AND A KNIGHT

00:38.538 --> 00:40.665
WERE RACING
TOWARD THE KINGDOM

00:40.749 --> 00:42.250
AT THE SAME TIME,

00:42.333 --> 00:44.210
WHICH ONE WOULD
GET THERE FIRST?

00:44.294 --> 00:45.378
OOH! OOH!

00:44.294 --> 00:45.378
{\an1}I KNOW!

00:45.462 --> 00:46.796
I KNOW. PICK ME.

00:45.462 --> 00:46.796
{\an3}BLAINE?

00:46.880 --> 00:48.465
THE KNIGHT,
OF COURSE,

00:48.548 --> 00:50.425
{\an1}ESPECIALLY
IF THAT KNIGHT IS ME.

00:50.508 --> 00:52.969
I'M AWESOME.

00:53.052 --> 00:54.971
ACCORDING TO
MY CALCULATIONS,

00:55.054 --> 00:57.807
{\an1}THE KNIGHT WOULD BE WAY
TOO SLOW WITHOUT A HORSE.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.893
{\an1}THE DRAGON WOULD
DEFINITELY GET THERE FIRST.

00:59.976 --> 01:02.061
{\an1}WELL, I WOULD
NEVER MAKE

01:02.145 --> 01:03.855
{\an1}A SILLY MISTAKE
LIKE THAT.

01:03.938 --> 01:06.065
BUT, AS A KNIGHT,
IF YOU DO

01:06.149 --> 01:07.984
MAKE A MISTAKE,
WHAT SHOULD YOU DO?

01:08.067 --> 01:10.695
{\an1}EASY. BLAME IT
ON SOMEONE ELSE.

01:10.779 --> 01:12.864
WOULDN'T IT BE BETTER
TO APOLOGIZE RIGHT AWAY

01:12.947 --> 01:16.868
AND DO YOUR BEST
TO MAKE IT RIGHT?

01:16.951 --> 01:18.661
GREAT ANSWER,
PRINCESS NELLA!

01:18.745 --> 01:19.996
{\an1}HMPH.

01:18.745 --> 01:19.996
[BELL RINGS]

01:20.079 --> 01:21.331
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

01:20.079 --> 01:21.331
BYE, GUYS.

01:21.414 --> 01:24.000
HAVE A ROYAL
WEEKEND, EVERYBODY.

01:24.083 --> 01:25.210
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:25.293 --> 01:26.753
HUP! HUP! HUP!

01:26.836 --> 01:28.046
TRINKET:
NELLA, NELLA...

01:28.129 --> 01:29.047
{\an1}CLOD:
GARRETT, LOOK.

01:29.130 --> 01:30.173
YOU'VE GOT
A PACKAGE.

01:30.256 --> 01:31.090
HEY, GUYS.

01:31.174 --> 01:32.300
YOU GOT ONE,
TOO, BUDDY.

01:32.383 --> 01:33.301
{\an1}OPEN IT, OPEN IT,
OPEN IT.

01:33.384 --> 01:36.596
BOTH: I HOPE THIS IS WHAT
I THINK IT IS.

01:36.679 --> 01:39.057
HEE! MY NEW NAIL POLISH--

01:39.140 --> 01:41.100
FUCHSIA SHIMMER
POLKA STRIPES.

01:41.184 --> 01:42.644
{\an1}OH! FUCHSIA SHIMMER
POLKA STRIPES?

01:42.727 --> 01:45.480
ISN'T IT AMAZING?

01:45.563 --> 01:48.233
{\an1}YOU SHOULD TRY IT OUT
RIGHT AWAY ON MY HOOVES.

01:48.316 --> 01:49.692
WHY NOT?

01:49.776 --> 01:51.194
ANY TIME'S
THE RIGHT TIME

01:51.277 --> 01:52.403
FOR A HOOFICURE.

01:52.487 --> 01:53.780
OH...

01:52.487 --> 01:53.780
OOH...

01:53.863 --> 01:55.365
PRETTY.

01:53.863 --> 01:55.365
PRETTY.

01:55.448 --> 01:57.325
GARRETT: WHOA.
LOOK WHAT I GOT--

01:57.408 --> 01:58.868
THE LATEST PACK OF
KNIGHTLY TRADING CARDS.

01:58.952 --> 02:00.870
CHECK OUT THE
CREATURES ON THESE--

02:00.954 --> 02:05.250
THE PEGASNAIL,
THE SPIDERSPHINX,

02:05.333 --> 02:07.877
EVEN
AN UNDERWEARWOLF.

02:07.961 --> 02:10.003
{\an1}UH, NOW,
THAT SOUNDS SCARY.

02:10.088 --> 02:13.883
{\an1}COACH: HEY, HEY, KNIGHTLY
TRADING CARDS, HUH?

02:13.967 --> 02:15.301
I USED
TO COLLECT THEM

02:15.385 --> 02:16.928
WHEN I WAS
JUST A SQUIRE.

02:17.011 --> 02:18.471
{\an7}REALLY?

02:17.011 --> 02:18.471
{\an8}SURE.

02:18.555 --> 02:21.349
IN FACT, I STILL
KEEP MY ALL-TIME

02:21.432 --> 02:24.394
FAVORITE CARD WITH
ME TO THIS VERY DAY,

02:24.477 --> 02:27.021
AH, A RARE CARD
OF THE RAREST

02:27.105 --> 02:30.024
OF CREATURES--
THE BAFFLIN.

02:30.108 --> 02:31.568
BOTH: THE BAFFLIN?

02:31.651 --> 02:33.570
{\an1}WHAT'S
A BAFFLIN?

02:33.653 --> 02:36.239
IT'S A STRANGE,
WILD CREATURE

02:36.322 --> 02:38.199
THAT LIVES
HIGH ATOP

02:38.283 --> 02:40.076
THE GREAT SKY
CLIFFS.

02:40.159 --> 02:42.579
WHOA!

02:40.159 --> 02:42.579
{\an1}WOW!

02:42.662 --> 02:44.747
OF COURSE, I'VE NEVER
SEEN ONE IN PERSON,

02:44.831 --> 02:47.000
ONLY THE PICTURE ON
THIS CLASSIC OLD CARD.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.544
SUCH A BEAUTIFUL
CREATURE.

02:49.627 --> 02:51.629
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE?

02:51.713 --> 02:53.423
{\an1}TOTALLY.

02:51.713 --> 02:53.423
TOTALLY. WHOOPS.

02:53.506 --> 02:55.383
[BOTH GASP]

02:55.466 --> 02:58.177
WHAT?

02:55.466 --> 02:58.177
OH, MY GOODNESS.

02:58.261 --> 03:01.598
THE CARD,
IT'S RUINED.

03:01.681 --> 03:03.725
BUT MY C--
OH, DEAR.

03:03.808 --> 03:06.227
{\an7}IT WAS
AN ACCIDENT.

03:06.311 --> 03:08.271
{\an8}WE DIDN'T MEAN
TO DO IT.

03:08.354 --> 03:12.191
OH, MY.
WELL, IT'S OK.

03:12.275 --> 03:14.611
ACCIDENTS
HAPPEN, I GUESS.

03:14.694 --> 03:17.238
IT WAS ONLY MY
FAVORITE THING

03:17.322 --> 03:19.407
IN THE WHOLE
WIDE WORLD.

03:19.490 --> 03:22.285
{\an1}I'M SORRY, SIR COACH.
I REALLY AM.

03:22.368 --> 03:24.037
ME, TOO.

03:24.120 --> 03:26.414
I KNOW. I JUST--

03:26.497 --> 03:28.625
UM, I'D BETTER
GET GOING NOW.

03:28.708 --> 03:31.085
HAVE A ROYAL
WEEKEND, EVERYONE.

03:31.169 --> 03:31.669
POOR SIR COACH.

03:31.753 --> 03:35.465
HE LOVES THAT CARD.

03:35.548 --> 03:37.091
[WIND BLOWING]

03:37.175 --> 03:39.469
THE CARD!

03:39.552 --> 03:40.929
{\an1}I FEEL JUST
AWFUL ABOUT IT.

03:41.012 --> 03:44.641
ME, TOO. BUT
WHAT CAN WE DO?

03:44.724 --> 03:45.808
IT WAS
AN ACCIDENT.

03:45.892 --> 03:47.560
{\an1}BUT WHEN YOU
MAKE A MISTAKE,

03:47.644 --> 03:49.938
{\an1}YOU'VE GOT TO DO YOUR BEST
TO MAKE IT RIGHT AGAIN.

03:50.021 --> 03:52.106
BUT HOW ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO THAT?

03:52.190 --> 03:53.566
I'LL TELL YOU HOW.

03:53.650 --> 03:55.652
WE'RE GOING TO
FIND THE BAFFLIN,

03:55.735 --> 03:57.654
TAKE ITS PICTURE,
AND PUT IT

03:57.737 --> 04:00.114
ON A NEW CARD
FOR SIR COACH.

04:00.198 --> 04:01.783
MY HEART IS BRIGHT!

04:01.866 --> 04:03.785
TIME TO BE A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

04:03.868 --> 04:05.745
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

04:05.828 --> 04:07.497
♪ IT'S TIME TO SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

04:07.580 --> 04:09.624
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

04:09.707 --> 04:11.250
♪ MY COURAGE SHINING BRIGHT ♪

04:11.334 --> 04:15.463
♪ NOW I AM
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

04:16.798 --> 04:21.219
{\an1}THERE'S NO MISTAKING THAT.
JUST DAZZLING.

04:21.302 --> 04:23.513
{\an1}COME ON.

04:21.302 --> 04:23.513
WHOO-HOO!

04:23.596 --> 04:24.847
GARRETT:
YEAH, NELLA.

04:24.931 --> 04:26.516
HOORAY!

04:30.144 --> 04:32.855
{\an1}UHH, THIS SURE IS
A LONG WAY UP.

04:32.939 --> 04:34.732
NELLA: JUST A FEW
MORE STEPS

04:34.816 --> 04:36.275
THROUGH
THESE CLOUDS,

04:36.359 --> 04:39.529
AND I THINK...
WE'RE HERE.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.197
WELCOME
TO THE SKY CLIFFS.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.241
{\an1}WHOA!

04:41.281 --> 04:43.241
WOW!

04:43.324 --> 04:45.493
TRINKET:
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

04:45.576 --> 04:47.537
{\an1}BUT HOW ARE WE GONNA
FIND THE BAFFLIN?

04:47.620 --> 04:50.373
YEAH. WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

04:50.456 --> 04:51.541
MAYBE THERE'S
A CLUE

04:51.624 --> 04:53.084
ON SIR COACH'S
OLD CARD.

04:53.167 --> 04:55.294
HMM,
IT LOOKS LIKE

04:55.378 --> 04:56.963
{\an1}IT HAS THE CLAWS
OF AN EAGLE...

04:57.046 --> 04:59.215
AND BUTTERFLY
WINGS...

04:59.298 --> 05:01.175
{\an1}AND THE TRUNK
OF AN ELEPHANT.

05:01.259 --> 05:03.094
[BAFFLIN TRUMPETS]

05:03.177 --> 05:05.221
WHAT WAS THAT?

05:05.304 --> 05:07.348
PLEASE TELL ME IT WASN'T
AN UNDERWEARWOLF.

05:07.432 --> 05:11.060
{\an1}GARRETT: IT SOUNDED MORE
LIKE AN ELEPHANT.

05:11.144 --> 05:13.771
THE BAFFLIN HAS A TRUNK
LIKE AN ELEPHANT.

05:13.855 --> 05:16.357
BOTH:
THAT MUST BE THE BAFFLIN!

05:16.441 --> 05:19.402
COME ON. WE NEED
TO FOLLOW THAT SOUND.

05:19.777 --> 05:22.363
LOOK.

05:22.447 --> 05:23.406
EAGLE AND HORSE PRINTS!

05:23.489 --> 05:26.576
THEY MUST BE THE
BAFFLIN'S FOOTPRINTS.

05:26.659 --> 05:29.203
LET'S FOLLOW THEM.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.540
GARRETT: THE CLOUDS
ARE GETTING DARKER.

05:32.623 --> 05:33.875
LOOKS LIKE A SKY CLIFFS
STORM MIGHT BE COMING.

05:33.958 --> 05:35.084
WE BETTER TAKE
THAT PICTURE

05:35.168 --> 05:36.294
AND GET BACK
SOON.

05:36.377 --> 05:39.088
UH, THE TRACKS STOP HERE.

05:39.172 --> 05:40.590
BUT NO BAFFLIN.

05:40.673 --> 05:42.133
YEAH. IT DOESN'T
MAKE SENSE.

05:42.216 --> 05:42.759
WHERE COULD IT
HAVE GONE?

05:42.842 --> 05:44.886
WAIT A MINUTE.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.095
{\an1}YOU SAID IT
BEFORE, NELLA.

05:46.179 --> 05:47.221
THE BAFFLIN HAS WINGS.

05:47.305 --> 05:49.932
{\an1}THE TRACKS MUST END
BECAUSE IT FLEW AWAY.

05:50.016 --> 05:52.477
[BAFFLIN TRUMPETS]

05:52.560 --> 05:54.437
THERE'S THAT
NOISE AGAIN.

05:54.520 --> 05:55.605
THE BAFFLIN, IT'S
GOT TO BE CLOSE.

05:55.688 --> 05:57.774
COME ON.

05:57.857 --> 06:00.234
NELLA: THERE IT IS,

06:00.318 --> 06:01.944
ON THE TOP OF THAT CLIFF.

06:02.028 --> 06:04.739
I'M GONNA SNEAK CLOSER
TO GET A REAL GOOD SHOT.

06:04.822 --> 06:06.991
[SNAP]

06:07.075 --> 06:08.284
[TRUMPETS]

06:08.367 --> 06:08.910
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

06:08.993 --> 06:10.536
GAUNTLETS! I MISSED.

06:10.620 --> 06:14.373
NOW WE'LL NEVER GET
SIR COACH'S PICTURE.

06:14.457 --> 06:15.124
LET ME TRY, GARRETT.

06:15.208 --> 06:18.836
GO, NELLA!

06:15.208 --> 06:18.836
HOLD ON. WAIT.

06:18.920 --> 06:22.006
OH, NO.
SHE'S FLYING EVEN HIGHER.

06:22.090 --> 06:24.300
I KNOW HOW
TO CATCH UP TO HER.

06:26.219 --> 06:28.971
HERE GOES.

06:29.055 --> 06:31.474
WHO-OA!

06:31.557 --> 06:33.810
WHOA! HA HA! WAIT UP.

06:33.893 --> 06:35.645
{\an1}WE JUST WANT TO
TAKE YOUR PICTURE.

06:35.728 --> 06:37.063
[TRUMPETS]

06:37.146 --> 06:41.317
{\an1}WHOA. HOW AM I GOING
TO FOLLOW YOU IN THERE?

06:41.400 --> 06:43.778
{\an1}THIS OUGHT
TO DO THE TRICK.

06:48.407 --> 06:50.868
HUP! WHOO-HOO!

06:50.952 --> 06:52.787
WHEW!

06:52.870 --> 06:55.748
WHERE DID YOU GO NOW?

06:55.832 --> 06:58.543
BAFFLIN? BAFFLIN?

06:58.626 --> 06:59.877
[GASPS]

07:01.796 --> 07:04.924
WOW. YOU'RE INCREDIBLE.

07:05.007 --> 07:08.845
WHO ARE YOU, AND WHY
ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME?

07:08.928 --> 07:11.430
{\an1}OH, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO SCARE YOU OR ANYTHING.

07:11.514 --> 07:13.641
{\an1}I'M NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT,

07:13.724 --> 07:15.601
{\an1}AND I WAS JUST
WONDERING IF MAYBE

07:15.685 --> 07:17.311
I COULD TAKE
YOUR PICTURE.

07:17.395 --> 07:18.855
WOULD YOU MIND?

07:18.938 --> 07:20.106
SORRY. I DON'T
REALLY LIKE

07:20.189 --> 07:21.858
HAVING MY
PICTURE TAKEN.

07:21.941 --> 07:23.943
{\an1}WHY NOT?

07:24.026 --> 07:25.820
FOR STARTERS,
I'VE GOT A TRUNK,

07:25.903 --> 07:27.155
BUT I'M NOT
AN ELEPHANT,

07:27.238 --> 07:28.030
AND I'VE GOT WINGS,
BUT I'M NOT A BIRD.

07:28.114 --> 07:30.783
I'M JUST SO--

07:30.867 --> 07:33.452
AMAZING.

07:33.536 --> 07:36.289
REALLY? GEE, THANKS.

07:36.372 --> 07:38.332
{\an1}THERE'S A LOT OF PEOPLE
WHO THINK SO.

07:38.416 --> 07:41.419
{\an1}IN FACT, MY TEACHER,
SIR COACH, HAPPENS TO BE

07:41.502 --> 07:43.504
{\an1}ONE OF YOUR
BIGGEST FANS.

07:43.588 --> 07:44.797
I HAVE FANS?

07:44.881 --> 07:48.050
[THUNDER]

07:48.134 --> 07:49.552
WHAT WAS THAT?

07:49.635 --> 07:50.761
[WIND BLOWING]

07:50.845 --> 07:53.181
{\an8}CLOD: THE WIND
IS GETTING STRONGER.

07:53.264 --> 07:55.558
{\an8}AND THESE STORM CLOUDS
ARE LOOKING DANGEROUS.

07:55.641 --> 07:57.727
{\an8}[THUNDER]

07:57.810 --> 08:00.396
{\an1}THIS WAY,
INTO THE CAVE.

08:00.479 --> 08:02.815
OH, NO.

08:00.479 --> 08:02.815
DON'T WORRY.

08:02.899 --> 08:04.817
THE STORM CAN'T
GET US WAY UP HERE.

08:04.901 --> 08:06.527
YEAH, BUT MY FRIENDS
ARE CAUGHT

08:06.611 --> 08:08.821
RIGHT IN
THE MIDDLE OF IT.

08:08.905 --> 08:10.698
OH, WE'RE SAFE.

08:10.781 --> 08:11.490
AND SOUND.

08:17.330 --> 08:18.915
{\an8}AND TRAPPED.

08:18.998 --> 08:22.084
NELLA: OH, NO.
THEY'RE TRAPPED IN THE CAVE.

08:22.168 --> 08:23.085
I'VE GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

08:23.169 --> 08:25.421
I SURE WISH THERE WAS
A WAY I COULD HELP.

08:25.504 --> 08:26.923
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:27.006 --> 08:28.674
I THINK THERE
JUST MIGHT BE.

08:28.758 --> 08:31.135
{\an1}COME ON.

08:31.219 --> 08:32.720
GARRETT: UH! UH!

08:32.803 --> 08:35.056
{\an8}THIS TREE'S
TOO BIG TO MOVE.

08:35.139 --> 08:37.183
{\an8}WE'LL BE
STUCK HERE FOREVER.

08:37.265 --> 08:39.101
OH, NO. WHO'S
GONNA SAVE US?

08:39.184 --> 08:41.938
[BAFFLIN TRUMPETS]

08:42.020 --> 08:45.358
NELLA: WHO-OA!

08:46.567 --> 08:47.777
IT'S NELLA.

08:47.860 --> 08:49.779
AND THE BAFFLIN, TOO.

08:49.862 --> 08:51.155
SEE IF YOU CAN
USE YOUR TALONS

08:51.239 --> 08:53.616
TO LIFT THE TREE,
BUT BE CAREFUL.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.994
NO PROBLEM.

08:58.788 --> 08:59.872
TERRIFIC!

08:59.956 --> 09:02.625
NOW LET'S GO
GET MY FRIENDS.

09:02.708 --> 09:03.793
COME ON UP.

09:03.876 --> 09:04.543
{\an7}HOLD ON TIGHT,
EVERYBODY.

09:04.627 --> 09:06.837
{\an7}I'LL GET YOU
TO SAFETY.

09:06.921 --> 09:07.964
YEAH!

09:06.921 --> 09:07.964
YAHOO!

09:08.047 --> 09:11.884
{\an1}NOW, LET'S GET OUT
OF THESE STORM CLOUDS.

09:16.138 --> 09:17.139
GARRETT: WOW.
THAT WAS AMAZING.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.559
YOU GOT
SUCH STRONG LEGS.

09:20.643 --> 09:22.562
TRINKET: AND SUCH
FABULOUS WINGS.

09:22.645 --> 09:24.105
CLOD:
AND WHAT A NOSE.

09:24.188 --> 09:26.774
{\an1}YEP. SHE'S ONE
OF A KIND, ALL RIGHT.

09:26.857 --> 09:28.359
AND--WAIT
A MINUTE--

09:28.442 --> 09:29.402
IS THAT
NAIL POLISH?

09:29.485 --> 09:34.073
{\an1}OH. YEAH--FUCHSIA
SHIMMER POLKA STRIPES.

09:34.156 --> 09:37.326
IT'S MY FAVE.

09:34.156 --> 09:37.326
{\an3}NO WAY.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.161
{\an1}TWINSIES!

09:37.410 --> 09:39.161
TWINSIES!

09:39.245 --> 09:41.414
WE HAVE GOT TO
TAKE A SELFIE.

09:41.497 --> 09:44.583
YOU MEAN, YOU DON'T MIND
IF WE TAKE YOUR PICTURE?

09:44.667 --> 09:46.127
OF COURSE NOT.

09:46.210 --> 09:47.336
I WANT TO REMEMBER
THIS DAY FOREVER.

09:47.420 --> 09:51.299
OK, EVERYBODY.
SAY, "CHEESE."

09:51.382 --> 09:51.924
{\an1}CHEESE!

09:51.382 --> 09:51.924
{\an3}CHEESE!

09:52.008 --> 09:54.176
{\an1}HA HA HA!

09:54.260 --> 09:54.927
[BELL RINGS]

09:55.011 --> 09:55.970
{\an1}GOOD MORNING,
SIR COACH.

09:56.053 --> 09:57.179
IS IT?

09:57.263 --> 09:59.682
WITHOUT MY
TRADING CARD,

09:59.765 --> 10:02.184
IT DOESN'T FEEL
VERY GOOD.

10:02.268 --> 10:04.854
{\an1}NELLA: SIR COACH, WE JUST
WANTED TO SAY AGAIN

10:04.937 --> 10:06.689
{\an1}HOW SORRY WE WERE
FOR RUINING

10:06.772 --> 10:08.816
YOUR TRADING CARD
THE OTHER DAY...

10:08.899 --> 10:10.484
THANK YOU, NELLA.

10:10.568 --> 10:12.903
I'M SURE I'LL GET OVER
IT IN A FEW YEARS.

10:12.987 --> 10:15.740
{\an1}AND SO WE HAVE A LITTLE
SURPRISE FOR YOU.

10:15.823 --> 10:16.532
WHAT'S THIS?

10:16.615 --> 10:20.161
THE BAFFLIN
ON A NEW CARD?

10:20.244 --> 10:22.747
YOU MEAN, YOU ALL
DID THIS FOR ME?

10:22.830 --> 10:24.498
A KNIGHT SHOULD
ALWAYS MAKE UP

10:24.582 --> 10:26.125
{\an1}FOR HIS OR HER
MISTAKES.

10:26.208 --> 10:28.711
{\an1}THAT'S WHAT YOU'VE
ALWAYS TAUGHT US, RIGHT?

10:28.794 --> 10:30.880
WE KNOW IT'LL NEVER
BE YOUR OLD CARD,

10:30.963 --> 10:33.716
BUT WE HOPE IT MAKES YOU
FEEL A LITTLE BETTER.

10:33.799 --> 10:35.593
IT'S REMARKABLE.

10:35.676 --> 10:36.427
THE PICTURE
IS AMAZING,

10:36.510 --> 10:38.429
SO MUCH BETTER
THAN MY OLD ONE.

10:38.512 --> 10:40.514
WHY, THIS MUST BE
THE NEXT BEST THING

10:40.598 --> 10:43.851
TO SEEING THE
BAFFLIN FOR REAL.

10:43.934 --> 10:45.686
SPEAKING OF WHICH,

10:45.770 --> 10:48.898
THERE'S ONE MORE SURPRISE
WE HAVE IN STORE FOR YOU.

10:48.981 --> 10:51.317
SIR COACH,
MEET THE BAFFLIN.

10:51.400 --> 10:54.570
PLEASE
CALL ME BAFFY.

10:54.653 --> 10:57.907
YA-HOO! WOWEE!

10:57.990 --> 11:00.576
{\an1}THIS IS A DREAM
COME TRUE.

11:00.659 --> 11:02.578
I THINK WE
MADE IT UP TO HIM.

11:02.661 --> 11:05.164
{\an1}YEP, AND IT SURE
FEELS GOOD.

11:05.247 --> 11:08.459
HEY, HOW ABOUT A PICTURE
OF ALL OF US TOGETHER?

11:08.542 --> 11:09.752
REALLY?

11:09.835 --> 11:11.253
{\an8}SAY, "BAFFLIN."

11:11.337 --> 11:12.671
{\an8}ALL: BAFFLIN!

11:12.755 --> 11:13.089
{\an8}[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

11:13.172 --> 11:15.257
[LAUGHTER]

11:15.341 --> 11:15.758
{\an1}NELLA: AW.

11:21.764 --> 11:22.932
[RINGING]

11:23.015 --> 11:24.475
{\an1}NELLA: IT'S TIME.
IT'S TIME.

11:24.558 --> 11:27.353
TRINKET: OH, MY GOSH, HURRY.
HE'S PROBABLY ALREADY HERE.

11:27.436 --> 11:28.187
GARRETT: WHO'S PROBABLY
ALREADY HERE?

11:28.270 --> 11:29.438
THE ICE-CREAM MAN?

11:29.522 --> 11:32.692
NELLA AND TRINKET:
HA HA! NO.

11:32.775 --> 11:34.693
{\an1}OR A 3-EYED,
FLYING FERB-A-LOOT?

11:34.777 --> 11:35.194
{\an1}OH, HOW MANY
GUESSES DO WE GET?

11:35.277 --> 11:36.612
UH, HELLO?

11:36.695 --> 11:39.448
WE'RE ON OUR WAY
TO SEE THE ONE,

11:39.532 --> 11:42.493
THE ONLY,
THE AMAZING...

11:42.576 --> 11:46.414
{\an8}BOTH: SIR HAMSWORTH
THE GREAT.

11:46.497 --> 11:47.998
{\an7}IN CASE YOU
COULDN'T TELL...

11:48.082 --> 11:50.376
{\an8}BOTH: WE'RE HIS
BIGGEST FANS.

11:50.459 --> 11:52.128
{\an8}SIR HAMSWORTH
THE GREAT IS HERE?

11:52.211 --> 11:53.170
{\an8}THE SIR HAMSWORTH?

11:53.254 --> 11:56.799
{\an1}THE BRAVEST KNIGHT
EVER TO ROAM THE KINGDOM?

11:56.882 --> 11:58.426
THAT'S THE ONE.

11:58.509 --> 12:00.970
THERE'S NO QUEST
HE CAN'T COMPLETE,

12:01.053 --> 12:02.138
NO DANGER HE WON'T FACE.

12:02.221 --> 12:04.348
NELLA: WHAT A HERO.

12:04.432 --> 12:05.808
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE'S RIGHT HERE

12:05.891 --> 12:06.892
IN CASTLEHAVEN

12:06.976 --> 12:08.561
FOR A SURPRISE
SCROLL SIGNING.

12:08.644 --> 12:10.187
[DISTANT CHEERING]

12:10.271 --> 12:11.647
LET'S GO, GUYS, OR ELSE
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.

12:11.730 --> 12:14.275
{\an1}YOU DON'T HAVE
TO TELL ME TWICE.

12:14.358 --> 12:16.819
{\an1}LET'S GO, GUYS, OR ELSE
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.

12:16.902 --> 12:18.779
{\an1}OOPS.
THAT WAS TWICE.

12:18.863 --> 12:21.198
COME ON, BUDDY.

12:22.658 --> 12:23.534
{\an3}HOORAY!

12:22.658 --> 12:23.534
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

12:23.617 --> 12:25.453
SIR HAMSWORTH!

12:23.617 --> 12:25.453
YEAH!

12:25.536 --> 12:26.579
LOOK. THERE HE IS.

12:26.662 --> 12:29.248
MAN: HEY, SIR HAMSWORTH,
OVER HERE!

12:29.331 --> 12:30.374
HA HA!

12:30.458 --> 12:32.376
HERE I AM TO
THRILL YOUR DAY--

12:32.460 --> 12:34.420
THE ONE, THE ONLY

12:34.503 --> 12:37.548
SIR HEATH HAMSWORTH
THE GREAT.

12:37.631 --> 12:39.758
HE'S HERE.
HE'S REALLY HERE.

12:39.842 --> 12:43.137
{\an1}HEATH: THERE YOU ARE.
DON'T WORRY, FOLKS.

12:43.220 --> 12:45.181
{\an1}I HAVE ENOUGH PICTURES
OF ME TO GO AROUND.

12:45.264 --> 12:47.349
HI!

12:47.433 --> 12:48.684
{\an8}UH, YOU DON'T KNOW ME,
SIR HAMSWORTH,

12:48.767 --> 12:50.561
{\an7}BUT I'M KIND OF, LIKE,
YOUR BIGGEST FAN.

12:50.644 --> 12:52.813
{\an8}I'VE STUDIED ALL YOUR
GREATEST KNIGHT MOVES,

12:52.897 --> 12:53.647
LIKE YOUR TRIPLE
TWIRL AND LUNGE.

12:53.731 --> 12:56.275
SEE? HYAH, HYAH, HYAH!
LUNGE.

12:56.358 --> 12:59.069
HOO-HOO! WELL DONE.

12:59.153 --> 13:01.614
PRINCESS NELLA IF
I'M NOT MISTAKEN.

13:01.697 --> 13:04.200
{\an8}YES. THAT'S ME.
DID YOU HEAR THAT, TRINK?

13:04.283 --> 13:05.576
{\an8}HE KNOWS MY NAME.

13:05.659 --> 13:09.205
UH, WILL YOU SIGN
MY PICTURE?

13:09.288 --> 13:12.374
{\an1}I MEAN, YOUR PICTURE,
YOUR PICTURE.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.918
IT WOULD BE AN HONOR,
YOUR HIGHNESS.

13:14.001 --> 13:17.338
{\an7}GARRETT: EXCUSE ME,
MR. SIR HAMSWORTH, SIR,

13:17.421 --> 13:19.381
{\an1}BUT COULD YOU MAYBE
TELL US ABOUT THE TIME

13:19.465 --> 13:22.635
{\an1}YOU MET THE GIANT
DRAGON, RUMBLEFANG?

13:22.718 --> 13:23.260
ALL: OOH!

13:23.344 --> 13:25.721
WELL, IF YOU INSIST...

13:25.804 --> 13:28.891
{\an1}♪ I'LL TELL YOU
A TALE OF BRAVERY ♪

13:28.974 --> 13:31.018
♪ SURE TO ADD TO MY FAME ♪

13:31.101 --> 13:31.977
♪ A TALE ABOUT
HOW BRAVE I AM ♪

13:32.061 --> 13:35.439
♪ AND WORTHY
OF MY FAMOUS NAME ♪

13:35.523 --> 13:39.235
{\an1}ALL: ♪ OOH, BRAVE,
BRAVE SIR HAMSWORTH ♪

13:39.318 --> 13:40.277
{\an1}HEATH: ♪ IT'S A STORY
OF HOW I SLAYED ♪

13:40.361 --> 13:41.946
{\an1}♪ THE MEANEST DRAGON
IN ALL THE LAND ♪

13:42.029 --> 13:44.990
{\an1}♪ THE MOST DREADFUL BEAST
YOU'VE EVER SEEN ♪

13:45.074 --> 13:47.409
{\an1}♪ THE TERRIBLE,
TERRIBLE RUMBLEFANG ♪

13:47.493 --> 13:51.497
{\an1}ALL: ♪ OOH, BRAVE,
BRAVE SIR HAMSWORTH ♪

13:51.580 --> 13:53.415
{\an1}♪ I FOUND THE BEAST,
GOBBLED DOWN A SNACK ♪

13:53.499 --> 13:55.417
{\an1}♪ AND, BRAVE AND BOLD,
I HELD MY GROUND ♪

13:55.501 --> 13:57.086
♪ HE GAVE HIS TAIL
A GIANT THWACK ♪

13:57.169 --> 13:58.963
{\an1}♪ AND IT RUMBLED,
RUMBLED ALL AROUND ♪

13:59.046 --> 14:02.800
ALL: ♪ OOH, BRAVE, BRAVE
SIR HAMSWORTH ♪

14:02.883 --> 14:05.386
{\an1}♪ I WAS NOT AT ALL
THE LEAST BIT SCARED ♪

14:05.469 --> 14:07.429
♪ INTO THE DRAGON'S PATH
I SPRANG ♪

14:07.513 --> 14:09.431
{\an1}♪ I DREW MY SWORD
AND TOSSED MY HAIR ♪

14:09.515 --> 14:12.142
♪ AND SAID, "AWAY FROM HERE,
RUMBLEFANG" ♪

14:12.226 --> 14:15.354
[THUNDERING FOOTSTEPS]

14:16.647 --> 14:18.566
[ALL GASP]

14:18.649 --> 14:21.068
CLOD: UH, IS THIS
PART OF THE SHOW?

14:21.151 --> 14:23.320
{\an8}I DON'T THINK SO.

14:23.404 --> 14:24.530
{\an8}WOMAN: I'M NOT
STICKING AROUND.

14:24.613 --> 14:25.948
{\an8}MAN: LET'S GET
OUT OF HERE.

14:26.031 --> 14:27.116
{\an8}OH, DEARIE!

14:27.199 --> 14:28.325
WAIT. WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHAT IS IT?

14:28.409 --> 14:31.954
IT'S RUMBLEFANG.

14:33.998 --> 14:36.250
YIKES!

14:36.875 --> 14:39.044
HEATH: OHH...OHH...

14:39.128 --> 14:41.130
ARE YOU OK,
SIR HAMSWORTH?

14:41.213 --> 14:42.131
OOH...OOH...OOH.

14:42.214 --> 14:46.093
UM, NELLA, MAYBE NOW
WOULD BE A GOOD TIME

14:46.176 --> 14:47.094
TO ASK SIR HAMSWORTH
TO HELP US.

14:47.177 --> 14:50.139
{\an1}YEAH. WHAT DO YOU
THINK, SIR HAMSWORTH?

14:50.222 --> 14:51.807
SIR HAMSWORTH?

14:51.890 --> 14:52.641
{\an1}OHH!

14:52.725 --> 14:54.643
NELLA: HEY, WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

14:54.727 --> 14:56.312
{\an1}OH, IT LOOKS
LIKE HE'S SCARED.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.897
BUT THAT CAN'T BE.
HE'S MY HERO.

14:58.981 --> 15:00.983
HE'S SUPPOSED
TO BE BRAVE.

15:01.066 --> 15:04.320
{\an1}MAYBE HE'S BRAVELY
RUNNING AWAY,

15:04.403 --> 15:06.822
{\an8}WHICH IS PROBABLY
WHAT WE SHOULD DO.

15:06.905 --> 15:10.326
THERE HE
GOES AGAIN.

15:10.409 --> 15:13.370
AND THERE GOES
MY MANE-DO.

15:13.454 --> 15:15.497
MM...

15:13.454 --> 15:15.497
WAIT A SECOND.

15:15.581 --> 15:17.625
SOMETHING'S
NOT RIGHT HERE.

15:17.708 --> 15:19.001
OHH...

15:19.084 --> 15:20.878
HEY THERE, BIG FELLA.

15:20.961 --> 15:25.007
{\an1}WHOA, THERE.
UM, NICE DRAGON?

15:25.090 --> 15:27.384
I LIKE
TO THINK SO,

15:27.468 --> 15:28.886
BUT NOBODY ELSE
DOES.

15:28.969 --> 15:32.139
{\an1}WELL, IF YOU'RE
SUCH A NICE DRAGON,

15:32.222 --> 15:34.183
{\an1}WHY ARE YOU SCARING
EVERYONE AWAY?

15:34.266 --> 15:36.352
AND FRIZZING OUT
THEIR HAIR?

15:36.435 --> 15:37.895
I'M NOT TRYING
TO SCARE ANYBODY.

15:37.978 --> 15:41.523
IT'S JUST THAT
THAT KNIGHT HAS BEEN

15:41.607 --> 15:44.234
TELLING EVERYONE
THAT I'M A BIG,

15:44.318 --> 15:47.071
SCARY MEANIE,
BUT I'M NOT.

15:47.154 --> 15:51.992
YOU MEAN SIR HAMSWORTH'S
STORY WASN'T TRUE?

15:52.076 --> 15:53.535
UH-UH, AND IF
HE KEEPS ON

15:53.619 --> 15:55.954
MAKING UP
STORIES ABOUT ME,

15:56.038 --> 15:59.500
NOBODY WILL WANT
TO BE MY FRIEND.

15:59.583 --> 16:01.043
[GASPS]

16:01.126 --> 16:01.669
THAT'S NOT FAIR.

16:01.752 --> 16:03.629
BUT WHAT
CAN I DO?

16:03.712 --> 16:06.840
EVERYBODY ALWAYS
RUNS AWAY

16:06.924 --> 16:07.925
WHEN THEY
SEE ME.

16:08.008 --> 16:12.262
{\an1}AND ALL BECAUSE OF WHAT
SIR HAMSWORTH SAID.

16:12.346 --> 16:14.556
WELL, THEN WE'RE
JUST GONNA HAVE TO PROVE

16:14.640 --> 16:17.518
{\an1}TO EVERYBODY THAT
SIR HAMSWORTH WAS WRONG

16:17.601 --> 16:21.855
AND SHOW THEM JUST HOW NICE
YOU REALLY ARE, RUMBLEFANG.

16:21.939 --> 16:23.107
REALLY?

16:23.190 --> 16:24.775
REALLY.

16:27.194 --> 16:28.404
{\an7}ARE YOU SURE
ABOUT THIS, NELLA?

16:28.487 --> 16:30.614
{\an8}OF COURSE.

16:30.698 --> 16:32.241
{\an8}ONCE PEOPLE SEE
RUMBLEFANG DOING

16:32.324 --> 16:35.244
{\an8}NICE THINGS, I KNOW
THEY'LL LOVE HIM.

16:35.327 --> 16:36.995
{\an8}HEY, IT'S OK,
EVERYONE.

16:37.079 --> 16:38.789
{\an8}RUMBLEFANG'S
NICE.

16:38.872 --> 16:40.290
HELLO!

16:40.374 --> 16:40.916
OH!

16:40.374 --> 16:40.916
UH!

16:40.999 --> 16:42.710
MAN: HE SEEMS MEAN.

16:42.793 --> 16:43.544
DIFFERENT MAN:
SIR HAMSWORTH WAS RIGHT.

16:43.627 --> 16:45.879
OK. I'M SCARED.

16:47.339 --> 16:49.049
{\an8}HE'S JUST
A LITTLE LOUD.

16:51.093 --> 16:52.094
GO AHEAD.

16:52.177 --> 16:54.805
JUST BE YOURSELF AND
EVERYONE WILL LIKE YOU.

16:54.888 --> 16:56.014
OHH...

16:57.141 --> 17:02.980
{\an1}ALLOW ME TO HELP YOU
WITH THOSE BAGS, MILADY.

17:03.063 --> 17:05.148
{\an8}OH, WHAT
A NICE DRAGON.

17:05.232 --> 17:06.358
{\an8}NELLA: SEE?
HE'S REALLY NICE.

17:06.442 --> 17:08.609
{\an1}OH, NO.

17:08.694 --> 17:11.946
{\an1}RUMBLEFANG'S BACK,
AND HE'S GOT MOTHER.

17:12.030 --> 17:13.449
HUH? OOPS.

17:13.531 --> 17:15.284
{\an1}LOOK OUT!
FRUIT ON THE LOOSE!

17:15.367 --> 17:16.785
OH, NO!

17:15.367 --> 17:16.785
AAH!

17:16.868 --> 17:18.871
{\an1}RUN!

17:16.868 --> 17:18.871
HUH?

17:18.954 --> 17:20.372
[THUD]

17:20.455 --> 17:23.416
HEY, YOU
WORK IT, CLOD.

17:23.500 --> 17:25.711
THAT LOOK IS SO IN.

17:25.794 --> 17:30.090
{\an1}AND SO IN MY MOUTH.
DELICIOUS. MMM!

17:30.174 --> 17:30.924
OOPS. I'M SORRY.

17:31.008 --> 17:32.676
HERE. LET ME
GET THAT FOR YOU.

17:32.760 --> 17:34.052
UH-OH. OOPS.

17:32.760 --> 17:34.052
{\an1}OH, NO.

17:34.136 --> 17:36.805
WATCH OUT. NO, NO. NO.
DON'T GO.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.891
HE'S NOT
A MEAN DRAGON.

17:38.974 --> 17:43.312
{\an1}BOY, THAT DID NOT
GO SO WELL.

17:43.395 --> 17:46.774
YOU'RE TELLING ME.
OHH...

17:46.857 --> 17:48.192
OHH...

17:48.275 --> 17:49.985
UHH...

17:50.068 --> 17:51.987
OH,
I'M SORRY.

17:52.070 --> 17:52.696
NO MATTER
WHAT I DO,

17:52.780 --> 17:55.532
I JUST MAKE
A MESS,

17:55.616 --> 17:58.577
AND EVERYONE
THINKS I'M MEAN.

17:58.660 --> 18:00.537
IT'S ALL
BECAUSE OF WHAT

18:00.621 --> 18:02.915
THAT SIR
HAMSWORTH SAID.

18:02.998 --> 18:05.834
{\an1}DON'T WORRY, RUMBLEFANG.
I'M NOT GONNA GIVE UP.

18:05.918 --> 18:08.253
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW HOW,
BUT WE'LL FIND A WAY

18:08.337 --> 18:10.047
{\an1}TO SHOW EVERYONE
THE TRUE YOU.

18:10.130 --> 18:14.301
BRIGADE CAPTAIN:
SOUND THE ALARM! DRAGON! DRAGON!

18:14.384 --> 18:16.345
DRAG--OH, NO.

18:14.384 --> 18:16.345
[CRACK]

18:16.428 --> 18:17.721
[WOOD CREAKING]

18:17.805 --> 18:20.557
{\an1}VENDOR: OH, NO! THE BELL,
IT'S GOING TO FALL.

18:20.641 --> 18:21.892
LOOK OUT!

18:20.641 --> 18:21.892
{\an1}OH, NO.

18:21.975 --> 18:22.935
{\an1}IT'S GOING
TO FALL.

18:23.018 --> 18:25.646
THE GOLDEN BELL
OF CASTLEHAVEN.

18:25.729 --> 18:27.856
{\an1}GARRETT: THAT BELL'S BEEN
IN THE KNIGHT BRIGADE TOWER

18:27.940 --> 18:28.857
FOR, LIKE, EVER.

18:28.941 --> 18:30.776
WE CAN'T
LET IT FALL.

18:30.859 --> 18:32.694
SIR HAMSWORTH
CAN HELP US.

18:32.778 --> 18:35.572
LOOK. THERE HE IS.

18:35.656 --> 18:36.490
I BETTER
GET OUT OF HERE

18:36.573 --> 18:39.284
BEFORE SOMEBODY
ASKS FOR MY HELP.

18:39.368 --> 18:41.662
{\an1}OH, PLEASE,
BRAVE SIR HAMSWORTH,

18:41.745 --> 18:43.664
YOU'VE GOT
TO HELP US.

18:43.747 --> 18:45.874
UH-OH. WHY, YES.
OF COURSE.

18:45.958 --> 18:49.419
I, SIR HAMSWORTH
THE GREAT,

18:49.503 --> 18:52.422
SHALL BRAVELY
SAVE THE BELL.

18:52.506 --> 18:54.758
MAN: YAY! GREAT.
THANK YOU, SIR HAMSWORTH.

18:54.842 --> 18:56.510
{\an1}THANK YOU,
SIR HAMSWORTH.

18:56.593 --> 18:59.179
I AM BRAVE AND BOLD.
I CAN DO THIS.

18:59.263 --> 19:02.808
YOU'VE GOT THIS, HAMMY,
NO PROBLEM.

19:02.891 --> 19:06.270
{\an1}IS HE REALLY
GOING TO HELP?

19:06.353 --> 19:07.855
UH...

19:08.605 --> 19:11.066
UH...BEHOLD.

19:11.149 --> 19:13.902
I'M ALMOST THERE.

19:13.986 --> 19:16.780
I'LL BE FINE
AS LONG AS I DON'T LOOK...

19:16.864 --> 19:17.447
DOWN!

19:17.531 --> 19:18.824
GAAH!

19:18.907 --> 19:21.285
OH, OH, WHOA, WHOA!

19:21.368 --> 19:22.411
OH!

19:21.368 --> 19:22.411
{\an1}OH, NO!

19:22.494 --> 19:23.704
{\an8}WE'VE GOT
TO HELP HIM.

19:23.787 --> 19:25.581
MY HEART IS BRIGHT!

19:25.664 --> 19:27.541
TIME TO BE A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

19:27.624 --> 19:29.668
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

19:29.751 --> 19:30.419
♪ IT'S TIME TO SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

19:30.502 --> 19:32.045
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

19:32.129 --> 19:34.006
♪ MY COURAGE SHINING BRIGHT ♪

19:34.089 --> 19:38.218
♪ NOW I AM
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

19:40.679 --> 19:43.432
NOW, THAT'S A HERO.

19:43.515 --> 19:44.266
{\an8}QUICK, RUMBLEFANG.

19:44.349 --> 19:46.727
{\an8}WE'VE GOT A KNIGHT
TO SAVE.

19:46.810 --> 19:49.187
RUMBLEFANG:
I'M READY TO RUMBLE.

19:50.898 --> 19:52.107
AAH!

19:52.190 --> 19:54.276
UP, UP, UP.

19:54.359 --> 19:56.904
{\an1}THERE HE IS,
RUMBLEFANG. QUICK.

19:56.987 --> 19:59.948
{\an1}OH, NO! NOW
THE BELL'S FALLING.

20:00.032 --> 20:03.076
{\an1}QUICK, WE'VE GOT
TO GRAB THAT, TOO.

20:09.207 --> 20:10.208
GOTCHA.

20:11.376 --> 20:14.338
AND NOW
I GOT IT.

20:14.421 --> 20:15.797
NICE CATCH,
RUMBLEFANG.

20:15.881 --> 20:17.299
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

20:15.881 --> 20:17.299
THAT WAS INCREDIBLE.

20:17.382 --> 20:20.385
ALAS, WHAT ABOUT ME?
WHOA!

20:20.469 --> 20:21.929
{\an1}UH-OH.
WE'RE NOT DONE

20:22.012 --> 20:24.556
{\an1}WITH THE RESCUING YET,
RUMBLEFANG.

20:24.640 --> 20:26.475
{\an3}HOLD ON!

20:24.640 --> 20:26.475
AAH!

20:26.558 --> 20:28.018
OH! OOH.

20:28.101 --> 20:30.395
SAVED BY THE BELL.

20:30.479 --> 20:31.521
YAY!

20:30.479 --> 20:31.521
HOORAY!

20:31.605 --> 20:32.940
{\an1}MAN: THANK YOU,
RUMBLEFANG.

20:33.023 --> 20:34.775
{\an8}THAT WAS...

20:34.858 --> 20:37.277
{\an8}AWESOME!

20:34.858 --> 20:37.277
{\an8}AWESOME!

20:37.361 --> 20:38.362
{\an8}SEE, EVERYONE?

20:38.445 --> 20:40.489
{\an8}RUMBLEFANG'S
REALLY NICE,

20:40.572 --> 20:43.241
{\an8}AND NOW HE'S
A HERO, TOO.

20:43.325 --> 20:44.660
IT'S TRUE.

20:44.743 --> 20:47.704
{\an1}NELLA AND RUMBLEFANG
ARE THE REAL HEROES HERE.

20:47.788 --> 20:50.499
{\an1}I'M NOT AS BRAVE
AS I PRETEND TO BE.

20:50.582 --> 20:51.458
AND?

20:51.541 --> 20:54.878
{\an1}OH. I'M SORRY
FOR TELLING EVERYONE

20:54.962 --> 20:57.673
YOU WERE MEAN,
RUMBLEFANG.

20:57.756 --> 20:59.299
IT WAS WRONG OF ME
TO MAKE UP STORIES.

20:59.383 --> 21:02.970
{\an1}CAN YOU EVER FORGIVE
